-- Colombia’s Central Bank Says It Would Prefer a Weaker Peso
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2012-02-15T16:30:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-15/colombia-s-central-bank-says-it-would-prefer-a-weaker-peso-1-.html
Colombia ’s central bank would like
to see a weaker peso, Juan Jose Echavarria, a co-director at the
monetary authority, told reporters in Bogota.  Interest rate increases have a minimal impact on the
exchange rate, he said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
 bschmidt16@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
